# =============================================================================
# What belongs in git vs local-only
# =============================================================================
#
# DO COMMIT (tracked in repo):
#   - Application source: src/, scripts/, tests/, main.py, requirements*.txt
#   - Public templates: config/*.example, .env.example, *.service.example
#   - Docs: README.md, docs/, *.md at repo root
#   - CI: .github/ (workflows), tooling configs that contain no secrets
#
# DO NOT COMMIT (this file ignores):
#   - Real config: paths, repo lists, tokens, webhooks → use *.example copies
#   - Vector DB / index artifacts (large; may mirror proprietary code)
#   - Logs, venvs, editor junk, env files with API keys
#
# After clone: copy examples → real config files (see docs/GITHUB_PUBLISH.md).
# =============================================================================

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# --- Virtual environments ---
venv/
env/
ENV/
.venv

# --- Secrets & local env (never push) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- IDE / OS ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Logs & runtime task logs ---
logs/
*.log
work_log.json
parallel_work_log.json

# --- Local config (machine paths, internal repo names, tokens in JSON) ---
# Keep the matching *.example files in git; copy to the real name locally.
config/repos_config.json
config/indexing_paths.json
config/tasks_config.json
config/config.json
config/notifications_config.json
config/ai_config.json
code-atlas.service

!config/repos_config.json.example
!config/indexing_paths.json.example
!config/tasks_config.json.example
!config/config.json.example
!config/notifications_config.json.example
!config/ai_config.json.example
!code-atlas.service.example

# --- Internal / host-specific dumps ---
config/services_mapping.json
config/skip_repos.json
!config/services_mapping.json.example
!config/skip_repos.json.example

# --- Vector DB, embeddings cache, reindex state (all under data/) ---
# Includes: data/qdrant_db/, reindex hashes, etc. Rebuild after clone.
data/

# --- Tests & coverage ---
htmlcov/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.pytest_cache/

# --- Temp / backup ---
*.tmp
*.bak
*.backup
